Many people, even me to some extent,  have the belief that artists should have a good grasp of traditional art styles as well as the principles of art (like balance and proportion). I think that cartoons take an amazing amount of creativity to make. Most cartoons have a ton of real world elements in them (scenery, buildings, animals) that take a lot of skill to translate to cartoon form.

As far as inferiority goes, people make cartoon out to be easy, but its really not. You have to follow the principles of art as well as your own rules that you made for your world. 

However, copying cartoon drawings and styles is easy. I personally find drawing existing cartoon and anime characters boring and unfulfilling as much as I love watching and reading about them.  I don't look down on people who draw them, but I find much more fulfillment in creating my own cartoons or painting landscapes
